crutch
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to push sheep under dipping fluid with the use of a crutch, a long pole with an S-shaped rod at the end, with which to pull and push sheep's heads.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
