Citations
Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author:
Vol / Page: 23
Edition:
Quote: crutch: a pole having at one end a slightly curved crosspiece and used to push sheep under as they swim through the dip. Hence the verb to crutch, to push sheep under.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1940
Source: Tale of NZ
Author: STUDHOLME
Vol / Page: 117
Edition:
Quote: One day whilst trying to 'crutch' (push under) some slippery-backed old ewe, my brother Geoffrey fell in amongst the sheep and got wet right over the top of his head.
